I"ê<p>If you want to get involved, you can:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Request access to join the discussion on Slack (see below)</li>
  <li>Participate in Friday meetings and Wednesday pull request review sessions (ask for more details in Slack)</li>
  <li>Submit pull requests on GitHub</li>
</ul>

<p>Questions, bug reports or suggestions can also be emailed to <a href="mailto:uadigital@email.arizona.edu">uadigital@email.arizona.edu</a> or (preferably!) reported on Slack.</p>

<h2 id="join-our-meetings">Join Our Meetings</h2>

<p>Arizona Digital hosts weekly meetings on Wednesdays and Fridays. Wednesday meetings are held on Zoom and dedicate the entire hour to reviewing and merging pull requests on <a href="/arizona-bootstrap/docs/0.0/about/get-involved/#review-or-contribute-code">GitHub</a>. Friday meetings are hosted in-person in UITS-116 (and can also be joined remotely via Zoom) and dedicate two hours to reviewing and merging pull requests, and covering topics concerning Drupal 8. For more details, connect with us on Slack on our <code class="highlighter-rouge">#friday-meetings</code> channel.</p>

<h2 id="connect-with-us-on-slack">Connect with Us on Slack</h2>

<p>The Arizona Digital team utilizes a variety of Slack channels ranging from general discussions to specific repos and products. You are welcome to join any and all of these channels. Below you will find all of our Slack channels and a description of the channelâ€™s purpose.</p>

